- Color palette unchanged from project standard

### Methods text
"Differential expression for the DIV2 vs DIV1 contrast was 
visualized as a volcano plot. The x-axis shows log2 fold 
change; the y-axis shows -log10 adjusted p-value (with no 
ceiling, ranging from 0 to 300 to capture the full dynamic 
range). Points are classified as 'Upregulated' (red, padj<0.05 
and |LFC|>0.585), 'Downregulated' (blue, same thresholds 
negative direction), or 'Not significant' (grey). The top 10 
genes in each direction (by adjusted p-value) are labeled."

